  "prompt": "Is my maternal cousin's maternal cousin, my cousin?",
  "response": "Yes, your maternal cousin's maternal cousin is also your cousin, but the exact relationship depends on how you and your maternal cousin's maternal cousin are connected.\n\nHere\u2019s how it works:\n1. Your maternal cousin is the child of your maternal aunt or uncle (your mother's sibling).\n2. Your maternal cousin's maternal cousin is either:\n   - Another child of your maternal aunt or uncle (making them your first cousin as well), or\n   - A child of your maternal aunt or uncle's sibling (making them your first cousin once removed).\n\nSo, in either case, they are still your cousin, though the specific degree of cousinhood may vary.",
